  <thing id="ioWoWIrCiC" name="Iron Circlet CL 10" description="In addition to functioning as a {i}hat of disguise{/i}, this circlet also makes it easy to scry upon the wearer if a talisman bound to these circlets is possessed. The wearer receives a -10 penalty on all saves against divination spells cast by the talisman&apos;s possessor.\n\nThis is of course identical to a traditional {i}hat of disguise{/i} save for aesthetics. In truth, the iron circlet is a far more powerful magic item more akin to a {i}cursed amulet of inescapable location{/i}. Its true statistics can only be revealed by use of the spell {i}analyze dweomer{/i}. A DC 30 Spellcraft skill check to identify magic items will reveal that there is something very odd about these iron circlets and they are not simply {i}hat of disguise{/i} analogues.\n\n{b}Construction\nRequirements{/b} Craft Wondrous Item, {i}disguise self{/i}, {i}nondetection{/i}{b}; Cost{/b} 18,400 gp" compset="Wondrous" summary="Alter appearance as with {i}disguise self{/i}. -10 penalty on all saves against divination spells">
