  <thing id="ioWoWEyOVi" name="The Eye of Vigilance (the First Eye of Vetra-Kali)" description="This jewel at first appears to be nothing more than an exquisite emerald worth at least 20,000 gp. Only if the jewel is steeped in the blood of a sentient creature does it reveal its true nature.\n\n{i}The Eye of Vigilance{/i} was the magical focus used to create the Horn of Abaddon in the first place and so it is connected to every square inch of the structure. The bearer of this jewel may scry the Horn of Abaddon just as if he possessed a {i}crystal ball{/i}. {i}The Eye{/i} is also a critical component of the ritual to destroy the {i}Silver Seal{/i} and return Vetra-Kali to the prime material plane.\n\nIf all three of the Eyes of Vetra-Kali are united in the statue of Vetra- Kali in the Sanctum, then the {i}Eye of Vigilance{/i} functions as a {i}crystal ball{/i} with {i}true seeing{/i} again limited to the confines of the Horn itself.\n\n{b}DESTRUCTION{/b} {i}The Eye of Vigilance{/i}, like all the Eyes of Vetra-Kali can only be destroyed by permanently slaying Vetra-Kali Eats-the-Eyes on his home plane. If this is ever done, the jewel shatters into emerald shatters worth a paltry 2,000 gp." compset="Wondrous" uniqueness="useronce">
