  <thing id="ioWoWOWith" name="The Withering Eye (the Third Eye of Vetra-Kali)" description="This jewel at first appears to be nothing more than an exquisite emerald worth at least 20,000 gp. Only if the jewel is steeped in the blood of a sentient creature does it reveal its true nature.{br}{br}{i}The Withering Eye{/i} was the magical focus used to first summon Vetra-Kali from the lower planes to the prime material.{br}{br}It is thus attuned to Vetra-Kali and a powerful channel for daemonic energy. {i}The Withering Eye{/i} when placed in the statue of Vetra-Kali {i}descrecates{/i} (as the spell except it affects both undead and daemons) the entire Horn of Abaddon. The DC to resist negative channeled energy within this area gains a +6 profane bonus. Every undead or daemonic creature gains a +2 profane bonus on all attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws. An undead or daemonic creature created within or summoned into such an area gains +2 hit points per HD.{br}{br}Furthermore, anyone who casts {i}animate dead{/i} within this area may create as many as double the normal amount of undead.{br}{br}The Eye is also a critical component of the ritual to destroy the Silver Seal and return Vetra-Kali to the prime material plane.{br}{br}If all three of the Eyes of Vetra-Kali are united in the statue of Vetra-Kali in the Sanctum, then the {i}Withering Eye{/i} not only {i}desecrates{/i} the Horn but also grants all daemons within fast healing 1.{br}{br}{b}DESTRUCTION{/b} {i}The Withering Eye{/i}, like all the Eyes of Vetra-Kali can only be destroyed by permanently slaying Vetra-Kali Eats-the-Eyes on his home plane. If this is ever done, the jewel shatters into emerald shatters worth a paltry 2,000 gp." compset="Wondrous" uniqueness="useronce">
