  <thing id="ioWoWEyOHa" name="The Eye of Hatred (the Second Eye of Vetra-Kali)" description="This jewel at first appears to be nothing more than an exquisite emerald worth at least 20,000 gp. Only if the jewel is steeped in the blood of a sentient creature does it reveal its true nature.{br}{br}{i}The Eye of Hatred{/i} was the magical focus used to dedicate the Horn of Abaddon to the Four Horsemen. It is thus sensitive to any outside interference. The {i}Eye of Hatred{/i} pulses whenever any divine magic of Mitran origin is used within the Horn of Abaddon. The Eye is also a critical component of the ritual to destroy the {i}Silver Seal{/i} and return Vetra-Kali to the prime material plane.{br}{br}If all three of the Eyes of Vetra-Kali are united in the statue of Vetra- Kali in the Sanctum, then the {i}Eye of Hatred{/i} not only pulses when such magic is used but immediately directs the {i}Eye of Vigilance{/i} to show that magic being used .{br}{br}{b}DESTRUCTION{/b} {i}The Eye of Hatred{/i}, like all the Eyes of Vetra-Kali can only be destroyed by permanently slaying Vetra-Kali Eats-the-Eyes on his home plane. If this is ever done, the jewel shatters into emerald shatters worth a paltry 2,000 gp." compset="Wondrous">
