  <thing id="fWoWConMas" name="Contract Master" description="You are skilled at negotiating with outsiders for their services.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Ability to cast {i}lesser planar ally, lesser planar binding{/i}, or a greater version of these spells.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Whenever you negotiate payment with an outsider to secure its services through {i}planar ally{/i}, {i}planar binding{/i}, or a similar spell, the cost of the payment is halved. In addition, receive a +4 bonus on any checks associated with such bargains or to compel service (such as with {i}planar binding{/i}). This bonus also applies when testing the trap of a {i}planar binding{/i} against the outsider&apos;s spell resistance. Finally, whenever you use a spell to gain or compel service from an outsider, you can attempt a Diplomacy skill check opposed by the outsider&apos;s Sense Motive.\n\nIf you succeed in this check, the contract you form with the outsider is worded in such a way to prevent the outsider from taking intentional actions that are harmful to you and your cause (subject to the GMs interpretation)." compset="Feat" uniqueness="useronce">
